        <para id="id2259958"><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>•</m:mo></m:math> Super-resolution
(Chapter 13).</para>
      </section>
      <section id="uid4">
        <title>Acknowledgments</title>
        <para id="id2259982">Some things do not change with new editions, in particular the
traces left by the ones that were, and remain important references for me.
As always, I am deeply grateful to Ruzena Bajcsy and Yves Meyer.</para>
        <para id="id2259991">I spent the last few years, with three brilliant and kind colleagues,
Christophe Bernard, Jérome Kalifa,
and Erwan Le Pennec, in a pressure cooker called a start-up.
Pressure means stress, despite very good moments.
The resulting sauce was a blend of what all of us could provide, and which
brought new flavors to our personalities. I am thankful to them for the
ones I got, some of which I am still discovering.</para>
        <para id="id2260007">This new edition is the result of a collaboration with Gabriel Peyré,
who made these changes not only possible, but also very interesting to do.
I thank him for his remarkable work and help.</para>
      </section>
